ground in Paris - online and on air over the next few weeks.\", \"from\": 338, \"to\": 483, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 338, \"end\": 341, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999947195113502, \"rank\": 5.280492748337046e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 433, \"end\": 438, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998299245, \"rank\": 1.7023452424804581e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Becky Sullivan  Quincy Hall celebrates winning the gold medal for the U.S. after competing in the Men's 400m final on Wednesday at Stade de France at the Paris Summer Olympics.Kirill Kudryavtsev/AFP via Getty Imageshide caption  NPR is in Paris for the 2024 Summer Olympics.\", \"from\": 485, \"to\": 759, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 485, \"end\": 499, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Becky_Sullivan\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Becky Sullivan\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Becky_Sullivan\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Becky_Sullivan\"}, {\"begin\": 501, \"end\": 507, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"score\": 0.999972908915868, \"rank\": 1.99027727451586e-05, \"text\": \"Quincy\", \"types\": [\"Q719456\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Quincy_Center_station\"}, {\"begin\": 688, \"end\": 693, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9996888799837681, \"rank\": 0.00016112870346586755, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}, {\"begin\": 714, \"end\": 717, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999947195113502, \"rank\": 5.280492748337046e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}, {\"begin\": 724, \"end\": 729, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998299245, \"rank\": 1.7023452424804581e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For more of our coverage from the Games head toour latest updates.\", \"from\": 760, \"to\": 826, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"SAINT-DENIS, France - The American runnerQuincy Hallwon the men's 400-meter final at the2024 Summer Olympics, reestablishing a U.S. claim on the event it once dominated.\", \"from\": 828, \"to\": 997, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 828, \"end\": 839, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999988144737, \"rank\": 1.185441345668033e-09, \"text\": \"SAINT-DENIS\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 854, \"end\": 862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992121296341935, \"rank\": 0.0006614327242900264, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It was another dramatic comeback at the Stade de France for the American runners.\", \"from\": 999, \"to\": 1080, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1063, \"end\": 1071, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992121296341935, \"rank\": 0.0006614327242900264, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"For much of the race, it seemed impossible that Hall could win it.\", \"from\": 1081, \"to\": 1147, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"He spent most of the first 200 meters race visibly lagging in sixth place.\", \"from\": 1148, \"to\": 1222, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Even as he came around the bend, with just 100 meters remaining, he was still in fourth place.\", \"from\": 1224, \"to\": 1318, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"But he labored to catch up - finally overtaking Great Britain's Matthew Hudson-Smith just before the finish line.\", \"from\": 1319, \"to\": 1432, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1367, \"end\": 1380, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 2.489123170014762e-14, \"text\": \"Great Britain\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain_at_the_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1383, \"end\": 1403, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Hudson-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I do not give up, man.\", \"from\": 1434, \"to\": 1457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I just grit.\", \"from\": 1458, \"to\": 1470, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I grind.\", \"from\": 1471, \"to\": 1479, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"I got determination.\", \"from\": 1480, \"to\": 1500, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Anything I can think of that's gonna get me to that line, I think of it,\\\" Hall said afterward.\", \"from\": 1501, \"to\": 1595, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"It wasn't that Hall had come off the block slowly, he said afterward.\", \"from\": 1597, \"to\": 1666, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Instead, it was his competitors - especially Hudson-Smith, who won silver, and bronze medalist Muzala Samukonga of Zambia - who had opened the race at a torrid pace.\", \"from\": 1667, \"to\": 1832, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1782, \"end\": 1788, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9894865720369908, \"rank\": 0.010621554400065871, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew these guys were gonna get out and they were gonna come for blood early.\", \"from\": 1834, \"to\": 1913, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"They were going to go out and try to see who they could throw off the race,\\\" Hall said.\", \"from\": 1914, \"to\": 2001, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"At last year's World Championships, it had been the Brit who bested Hall.\", \"from\": 2003, \"to\": 2076, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I knew that the last 50 was going to determine who wins the Olympics,\\\" said Hudson-Smith after the race Wednesday.\", \"from\": 2077, \"to\": 2192, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"He got that one step on me in the last 50, and that's all she wrote.\\\"\", \"from\": 2193, \"to\": 2263, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"In the end, the three top times in the final were also the three fastest times recorded worldwide this year.\", \"from\": 2265, \"to\": 2373, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"And they now make up three of the seven fastest times ever recorded at an Olympics.\", \"from\": 2374, \"to\": 2457, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"Quincy's one hell of an athlete,\\\" said Hudson-Smith.\", \"from\": 2459, \"to\": 2512, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I have been saying all year, 'If you are going to win, you have got to take it from me,' and that's exactly what he did.\\\"\", \"from\": 2513, \"to\": 2635, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"U.S.'s Quincy Hall (L), sprints ahead of Britain's Matthew Hudson-Smith (C) and Zambia's Muzala Samukonga (R) to win gold in the men's 400m final at Stade de France in Saint-Denis, north of Paris.Andrej Isakovic/AFP via Getty Imageshide caption  For decades, the U.S. had dominated the men's 400-meter race, winning seven Olympics in a row from 1984 through 2008.\", \"from\": 2637, \"to\": 3000, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2678, \"end\": 2685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"score\": 0.9997914911895941, \"rank\": 0.00020831037267854912, \"text\": \"Britain\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Great_Britain\"}, {\"begin\": 2688, \"end\": 2708, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Matthew Hudson-Smith\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Matthew_Hudson-Smith\"}, {\"begin\": 2717, \"end\": 2723, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.9894865720369908, \"rank\": 0.010621554400065871, \"text\": \"Zambia\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Zambia_national_football_team\"}, {\"begin\": 2805, \"end\": 2816, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999988144737, \"rank\": 1.185441345668033e-09, \"text\": \"Saint-Denis\", \"types\": [\"Q41176\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Stade_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 2857, \"end\": 2862, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"score\": 0.9996888799837681, \"rank\": 0.00016112870346586755, \"text\": \"Getty\", \"types\": [\"Q4830453\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Getty_Images\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"But since then, American runners had struggled in the event, placing third only once.\", \"from\": 3001, \"to\": 3086, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3017, \"end\": 3025, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992121296341935, \"rank\": 0.0006614327242900264, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Now, the gold is back in American hands, for the 20th time in Olympic history.\", \"from\": 3087, \"to\": 3165, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3112, \"end\": 3120, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"score\": 0.9992121296341935, \"rank\": 0.0006614327242900264, \"text\": \"American\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall's mark of 43.4 seconds was a personal best for the 26-year-old runner, and it was the fifth-fastest time ever recorded.\", \"from\": 3167, \"to\": 3291, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Afterward, Hall removed his shoes and did a victory lap around the stadium, with an American flag draped over his shoulders.\", \"from\": 3292, \"to\": 3416, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3376, \"end\": 3389, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 6.0526845698989575e-15, \"text\": \"American flag\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Flag_of_the_United_States\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Asked by a reporter at what point he knew he'd won, Hall answered confidently: \\\"As soon as they shot that gun, I knew I had it.\\\"\", \"from\": 3418, \"to\": 3546, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The comeback has become a signature feature of the men of Team USA here at the Paris track and field events.\", \"from\": 3548, \"to\": 3656, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3606, \"end\": 3614, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"score\": 0.948039382001726, \"rank\": 0.05480809341370677, \"text\": \"Team USA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/United_States_national_team\"}, {\"begin\": 3627, \"end\": 3632, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 0.9999999998299245, \"rank\": 1.7023452424804581e-10, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Earlier in the week, sprinter Noah Lyles won gold in the 100-meter after spending the first 30 meters in last place.\", \"from\": 3657, \"to\": 3773, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 3687, \"end\": 3697, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Noah Lyles\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Noah_Lyles\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Then, in Tuesday's 1500-meter final, Cole Hocker seized an unlikely window of opportunity to snatch the win from the race's two favorites.\", \"from\": 3774, \"to\": 3912, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall once competed primarily as a hurdler.\", \"from\": 3914, \"to\": 3956, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"As a runner at the University of South Carolina, he was an NCAA champion in the 400-meter hurdles.\", \"from\": 3957, \"to\": 4055, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4016, \"end\": 4029, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\", \"score\": 0.9999999998149178, \"rank\": 1.851641419070279e-10, \"text\": \"NCAA champion\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NCAA_Men's_Outdoor_Track_and_Field_Championship\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Over the past two years, he has put his energy into the 400-meter race instead.\", \"from\": 4056, \"to\": 4135, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"On Wednesday, he called the switch \\\"the best decision of my life.\\\"\", \"from\": 4137, \"to\": 4203, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Hall will compete in one more event at this Olympics, the men's 4x400-meter relay race.\", \"from\": 4205, \"to\": 4292, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"The relay heats begin Friday, and the final is on Saturday.\", \"from\": 4293, \"to\": 4352, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"Loading...  An earlier version of this story misstated the last name of Cole Hocker as Harper.\", \"from\": 4354, \"to\": 4448, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4426, \"end\": 4437, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Cole Hocker\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Cole_Hocker\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Sponsor Message  Become an NPR sponsor\", \"from\": 4450, \"to\": 4488, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 4477, \"end\": 4480, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"score\": 0.9999947195113502, \"rank\": 5.280492748337046e-06, \"text\": \"NPR\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/NPR\"}]}]}"